n that might reference node/g_clock)\n# Actually, the 'node' not declared errors happen in callbacks where node->now() was used.\n# In those cases, g_clock is available. Let's check for any remaining node->now() in callbacks.\n# (The python script earlier already replaced most of them)\n\nwith open(path, 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\n\nprint(\"Fixed spline_keyboard_vel_controller.cpp\")\nPYEOF"}}
